{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QGngkxHQe8j7tGkwvSUSGf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 5)\n     2→\n     3→### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — create-story (2026-03-23T12:14Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Observation: ACs 1-3 are already implemented.** Code for `getStackLabel('rust')`, `getCoverageTool('rust')`, and the Rust branch in `generateAgentsMdContent()` was added in earlier stories. Only AC4 (`getProjectName` Cargo.toml parsing) is new work.\n     6→- **Risk: Cargo.toml parsing edge cases.** Simple regex parsing without a TOML parser could break on comments, inline tables, or multi-line strings. Known tradeoff per NFR4.\n     7→- **Workaround: sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent.** Had to manually update status to `ready-for-dev`.\n     8→\n     9→### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — dev-story (2026-03-23T12:18Z)\n    10→\n    11→No issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.\n    12→\n    13→### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — code-review (2026-03-23T12:25Z)\n    14→\n    15→- **HIGH: Cargo.toml regex only matched double-quoted values.** Single quotes are valid TOML. Fixed to support both.\n    16→- **HIGH: Cargo.toml section regex broke on `[` in values.** Fixed to use `[\\s\\S]*?` with lookahead for next section.\n    17→- **HIGH: Missing showboat proof document.** Created.\n    18→- **MEDIUM: Test assertion too weak** for dependencies-only Cargo.toml. Fixed to verify actual fallback value.\n    19→- **MEDIUM: No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field.** Added.\n    20→- **LOW (not fixed): Mixed quote regex doesn't enforce matching quotes** — acceptable for simple parser per NFR3.\n    21→- **LOW (not fixed): Pre-existing uncovered lines 180, 221-222** in docs-scaffold.ts (unrelated to 8-8).\n    22→\n    23→### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — verification (2026-03-23T12:30Z)\n    24→\n    25→- All 7 ACs passed. Verifier used a Node.js script (`verify-acs.mjs`) to import and test the functions directly from the dist bundle — creative approach.\n    26→- **OBSERVABILITY GAP on all ACs:** No log events detected for any of the docs-scaffold function calls. These are pure utility functions with no instrumentation — expected for documentation scaffolding.\n    27→- **AC7 indirect:** Test source files not shipped in npm package, so vitest/bats couldn't run in container. Verified indirectly via all 6 functional ACs passing + dev agent's test report.\n    28→\n    29→### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — create-story (2026-03-23T08:35Z)\n    30→\n    31→- **Risk: Semgrep Rust pattern matching for match arms and closures can be finicky.** AC2 and AC3 depend on this — dev agent should validate rules carefully.\n    32→- **Risk: AC4 tagged integration-required** — verifying `codeharness audit` picks up Rust rules requires a real Rust project with Semgrep installed.\n    33→- **Observation: Pure-config story** — no TypeScript changes, just 3 YAML files. Clean scope.\n    34→- **Observation: computeSummary() rule-name mismatch** — existing analyzer.ts hardcodes JS/TS rule names. New Rust rule IDs won't match, so summary percentages will be off for Rust projects. Outside story scope but a follow-up candidate.\n    35→\n    36→### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — dev-story (2026-03-23T08:43Z)\n    37→\n    38→- **Semgrep validation broken locally:** `semgrep --validate` crashes with `Bigarray.create: negative dimension` on semgrep-core 1.136.0 on macOS. System-wide issue, not rule-specific. Structural validation done via YAML parsing in vitest.\n    39→- **computeSummary won't count Rust rule IDs:** `matchesRule()` in analyzer.ts only recognizes JS/TS rule names. Rust rule IDs won't be counted in summary stats. Architectural limitation — future story needed.\n    40→- **Large rule file:** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` is ~230 lines due to combinatorial explosion. Within NFR1 limit but verbose. Semgrep doesn't support wildcard matching across visibility/async modifiers.\n    41→\n    42→### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — code-review (2026-03-23T08:48Z)\n    43→\n    44→- **HIGH (fixed):** Test fixture missing `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case. Only bare `trace!()` was tested — a regression in `pattern-not` for namespaced form would go undetected. Fixed.\n    45→- **LOW (not fixed):** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit) due to N*M pattern explosion. Could be refactored with `pattern-not-inside` in future.\n    46→- **LOW (not fixed):** Error path rules only exclude `error!/warn!` levels, not `info!/debug!`. Matches JS/TS precedent but may cause false positives for devs logging errors at info level.\n    47→- **Coverage gap:** `computeSummary()` won't recognize Rust rule IDs — follow-up story needed.\n    48→\n    49→### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — verification (2026-03-23T08:54Z)\n    50→\n    51→- **AC2 FAIL:** `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` has invalid Rust pattern syntax. `Err($E) => { ... }` is not a standalone expression — match arms only exist inside `match` blocks. Semgrep parse error: `Stdlib.Parsing.Parse_error`. Zero findings on any input.\n    52→- **Root cause:** Dev agent couldn't run `semgrep --validate` locally (macOS Bigarray crash). Relied on YAML-parsing unit tests which don't validate Semgrep pattern syntax.\n    53→- **Fix needed:** Wrap match arm patterns inside full `match` expressions, e.g. `match $X { Err($E) => { ... } }` or use `pattern-inside` with a `match` block.\n    54→- **AC1, AC3, AC4 PASS.** AC5 partial (tests not shipped in container, CLI functional).\n    55→- Story returned to `in-progress` for AC2 fix.\n    56→\n    57→### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — dev-story fix cycle (2026-03-23T09:00Z)\n    58→\n    59→- **Semgrep not installed locally** — Cannot run `semgrep --validate` to confirm the rule parses correctly at the Semgrep engine level. The fix is structurally correct (match arms must be inside match blocks), but full validation requires semgrep-core.\n    60→- No workarounds, no tech debt added. Single-file YAML fix.\n    61→\n    62→### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — code-review fix cycle (2026-03-23T09:03Z)\n    63→\n    64→- **HIGH (fixed):** Test suite did not verify the `match $X { ... }` wrapper in `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` patterns — AC2 fix could be reverted without test failure. Added guard assertions.\n    65→- **MEDIUM (design gap, not fixed):** `computeSummary()` in `analyzer.ts` does not recognize Rust rule IDs. Out of scope per story constraints.\n    66→- **LOW (not fixed):** Catch/error-path rules only exclude `error!`/`warn!` levels. By-design per AC wording.\n    67→- **LOW (not fixed):** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit).\n    68→\n    69→### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — verification fix cycle 2 (2026-03-23T09:08Z)\n    70→\n    71→- **INFRA: Docker image cached stale npm pack** — First verification attempt failed because `codeharness verify-env build` used a cached image that didn't include the new Rust rule files. Had to force `docker rmi` + rebuild. Root cause: dist hash cache invalidation only tracks `dist/` changes, not `patches/` changes.\n    72→- **AC2 STILL BROKEN after dev fix** — The `match $X { ... Err($E) => { ... } ... }` pattern also fails Semgrep's Rust parser. Ellipsis (`...`) inside match blocks is not supported. Required manual experimentation in Docker to find the working syntax: `match $X { Err($E) => { ... } }` (no ellipsis between arms — Semgrep matches the Err arm regardless of other arms).\n    73→- **Proof format mismatch** — Verifier output used mixed command+output in single code blocks. `codeharness verify` parser requires separate ```bash and ```output blocks. Had to manually reformat the proof.\n    74→\n    75→### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — verification pass (2026-03-23T09:19Z)\n    76→\n    77→- All 5 ACs passed on third verification attempt after fixing both the Semgrep pattern syntax and Docker image caching.\n    78→- Total verify-dev cycles for story: 3 (initial fail on Err pattern → wrap in match → fix match ellipsis syntax)\n    79→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"f6bbd6de-72a9-4e2d-9c66-5ccb990b72c9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:04:49.381Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 5)\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — create-story (2026-03-23T12:14Z)\n\n- **Observation: ACs 1-3 are already implemented.** Code for `getStackLabel('rust')`, `getCoverageTool('rust')`, and the Rust branch in `generateAgentsMdContent()` was added in earlier stories. Only AC4 (`getProjectName` Cargo.toml parsing) is new work.\n- **Risk: Cargo.toml parsing edge cases.** Simple regex parsing without a TOML parser could break on comments, inline tables, or multi-line strings. Known tradeoff per NFR4.\n- **Workaround: sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent.** Had to manually update status to `ready-for-dev`.\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — dev-story (2026-03-23T12:18Z)\n\nNo issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — code-review (2026-03-23T12:25Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Cargo.toml regex only matched double-quoted values.** Single quotes are valid TOML. Fixed to support both.\n- **HIGH: Cargo.toml section regex broke on `[` in values.** Fixed to use `[\\s\\S]*?` with lookahead for next section.\n- **HIGH: Missing showboat proof document.** Created.\n- **MEDIUM: Test assertion too weak** for dependencies-only Cargo.toml. Fixed to verify actual fallback value.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field.** Added.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Mixed quote regex doesn't enforce matching quotes** — acceptable for simple parser per NFR3.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Pre-existing uncovered lines 180, 221-222** in docs-scaffold.ts (unrelated to 8-8).\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — verification (2026-03-23T12:30Z)\n\n- All 7 ACs passed. Verifier used a Node.js script (`verify-acs.mjs`) to import and test the functions directly from the dist bundle — creative approach.\n- **OBSERVABILITY GAP on all ACs:** No log events detected for any of the docs-scaffold function calls. These are pure utility functions with no instrumentation — expected for documentation scaffolding.\n- **AC7 indirect:** Test source files not shipped in npm package, so vitest/bats couldn't run in container. Verified indirectly via all 6 functional ACs passing + dev agent's test report.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — create-story (2026-03-23T08:35Z)\n\n- **Risk: Semgrep Rust pattern matching for match arms and closures can be finicky.** AC2 and AC3 depend on this — dev agent should validate rules carefully.\n- **Risk: AC4 tagged integration-required** — verifying `codeharness audit` picks up Rust rules requires a real Rust project with Semgrep installed.\n- **Observation: Pure-config story** — no TypeScript changes, just 3 YAML files. Clean scope.\n- **Observation: computeSummary() rule-name mismatch** — existing analyzer.ts hardcodes JS/TS rule names. New Rust rule IDs won't match, so summary percentages will be off for Rust projects. Outside story scope but a follow-up candidate.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — dev-story (2026-03-23T08:43Z)\n\n- **Semgrep validation broken locally:** `semgrep --validate` crashes with `Bigarray.create: negative dimension` on semgrep-core 1.136.0 on macOS. System-wide issue, not rule-specific. Structural validation done via YAML parsing in vitest.\n- **computeSummary won't count Rust rule IDs:** `matchesRule()` in analyzer.ts only recognizes JS/TS rule names. Rust rule IDs won't be counted in summary stats. Architectural limitation — future story needed.\n- **Large rule file:** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` is ~230 lines due to combinatorial explosion. Within NFR1 limit but verbose. Semgrep doesn't support wildcard matching across visibility/async modifiers.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — code-review (2026-03-23T08:48Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Test fixture missing `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case. Only bare `trace!()` was tested — a regression in `pattern-not` for namespaced form would go undetected. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit) due to N*M pattern explosion. Could be refactored with `pattern-not-inside` in future.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Error path rules only exclude `error!/warn!` levels, not `info!/debug!`. Matches JS/TS precedent but may cause false positives for devs logging errors at info level.\n- **Coverage gap:** `computeSummary()` won't recognize Rust rule IDs — follow-up story needed.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — verification (2026-03-23T08:54Z)\n\n- **AC2 FAIL:** `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` has invalid Rust pattern syntax. `Err($E) => { ... }` is not a standalone expression — match arms only exist inside `match` blocks. Semgrep parse error: `Stdlib.Parsing.Parse_error`. Zero findings on any input.\n- **Root cause:** Dev agent couldn't run `semgrep --validate` locally (macOS Bigarray crash). Relied on YAML-parsing unit tests which don't validate Semgrep pattern syntax.\n- **Fix needed:** Wrap match arm patterns inside full `match` expressions, e.g. `match $X { Err($E) => { ... } }` or use `pattern-inside` with a `match` block.\n- **AC1, AC3, AC4 PASS.** AC5 partial (tests not shipped in container, CLI functional).\n- Story returned to `in-progress` for AC2 fix.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — dev-story fix cycle (2026-03-23T09:00Z)\n\n- **Semgrep not installed locally** — Cannot run `semgrep --validate` to confirm the rule parses correctly at the Semgrep engine level. The fix is structurally correct (match arms must be inside match blocks), but full validation requires semgrep-core.\n- No workarounds, no tech debt added. Single-file YAML fix.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — code-review fix cycle (2026-03-23T09:03Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Test suite did not verify the `match $X { ... }` wrapper in `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` patterns — AC2 fix could be reverted without test failure. Added guard assertions.\n- **MEDIUM (design gap, not fixed):** `computeSummary()` in `analyzer.ts` does not recognize Rust rule IDs. Out of scope per story constraints.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Catch/error-path rules only exclude `error!`/`warn!` levels. By-design per AC wording.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit).\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — verification fix cycle 2 (2026-03-23T09:08Z)\n\n- **INFRA: Docker image cached stale npm pack** — First verification attempt failed because `codeharness verify-env build` used a cached image that didn't include the new Rust rule files. Had to force `docker rmi` + rebuild. Root cause: dist hash cache invalidation only tracks `dist/` changes, not `patches/` changes.\n- **AC2 STILL BROKEN after dev fix** — The `match $X { ... Err($E) => { ... } ... }` pattern also fails Semgrep's Rust parser. Ellipsis (`...`) inside match blocks is not supported. Required manual experimentation in Docker to find the working syntax: `match $X { Err($E) => { ... } }` (no ellipsis between arms — Semgrep matches the Err arm regardless of other arms).\n- **Proof format mismatch** — Verifier output used mixed command+output in single code blocks. `codeharness verify` parser requires separate ```bash and ```output blocks. Had to manually reformat the proof.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — verification pass (2026-03-23T09:19Z)\n\n- All 5 ACs passed on third verification attempt after fixing both the Semgrep pattern syntax and Docker image caching.\n- Total verify-dev cycles for story: 3 (initial fail on Err pattern → wrap in match → fix match ellipsis syntax)\n","numLines":79,"startLine":1,"totalLines":79}}}
