{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vn5R54nQsdnNd1J3CDkzNF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 9-1: Multi-stack detection with subdirectory scanning\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer with a monorepo containing multiple languages,\n     8→I want codeharness to detect all stacks in my project,\n     9→So that every language gets harness features instead of just the first detected.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a project with `package.json` AND `Cargo.toml` at root, when `detectStacks()` is called, then it returns `[{ stack: 'nodejs', dir: '.' }, { stack: 'rust', dir: '.' }]` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a monorepo with `frontend/package.json` and `backend/Cargo.toml`, when `detectStacks()` is called, then it returns `[{ stack: 'nodejs', dir: 'frontend' }, { stack: 'rust', dir: 'backend' }]` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a single-stack project with only `package.json`, when `detectStacks()` is called, then it returns `[{ stack: 'nodejs', dir: '.' }]` and `detectStack()` compat wrapper returns `'nodejs'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC4: Given an empty directory, when `detectStacks()` is called, then it returns `[]` and `detectStack()` compat wrapper returns `null` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC5: Given a project with `node_modules/some-package/Cargo.toml`, when `detectStacks()` scans subdirectories, then `node_modules` is skipped (no false positive) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC6: Given root has `package.json` and subdir `api/` has `Cargo.toml`, when `detectStacks()` is called, then root stacks appear first, subdir stacks after, sorted alphabetically by dir name <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→\n    20→## Technical Notes\n    21→\n    22→### New type to define\n    23→\n    24→Add to `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`:\n    25→\n    26→```ts\n    27→export interface StackDetection { stack: string; dir: string; }\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→### Changes to `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`\n    31→\n    32→The current `detectStack()` function (L7-14) does an early-return on the first match. The new `detectStacks(dir)` function must:\n    33→\n    34→1. **Root scan (no early return):** Check root for ALL stack markers (`package.json` for nodejs, `requirements.txt`/`pyproject.toml`/`setup.py` for python, `Cargo.toml` for rust). Collect all matches into `StackDetection[]` with `dir: '.'`.\n    35→2. **Subdirectory scan (1 level deep):** Use `readdirSync(dir, { withFileTypes: true })` to list immediate children. Filter `dirent.isDirectory()`. Skip directories in the skip list: `node_modules`, `.git`, `target`, `__pycache__`, `dist`, `build`, `coverage`. For each remaining directory, check for stack markers the same way as root.\n    36→3. **Ordering:** Root stacks first in priority order (nodejs > python > rust), then subdir stacks sorted alphabetically by dir name.\n    37→4. **Compat wrapper:** Keep `detectStack()` returning `string | null`. Implementation: `return detectStacks(dir)[0]?.stack ?? null`.\n    38→\n    39→`detectAppType()` (L100) signature stays unchanged — it is called per-stack by the orchestrator.\n    40→\n    41→### Test file\n    42→\n    43→Create/update `src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts`:\n    44→- Mock `readdirSync` and `existsSync` via `vi.mock('node:fs')` to simulate monorepo directory structures.\n    45→- Test cases: dual root stacks, monorepo layout, single-stack compat, empty dir, skip list enforcement, ordering.\n    46→\n    47→## Files to Change\n    48→\n    49→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Add `StackDetection` interface, add `detectStacks()` function, refactor `detectStack()` to be a compat wrapper delegating to `detectStacks()`\n    50→- `src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts` — Add multi-stack detection tests (root dual-stack, monorepo layout, empty dir, skip list, ordering, compat wrapper)\n    51→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CtXjRtoqF7483fGksk6Zn3","session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"ed22d539-b327-4caf-b8fe-90ee11e5a3cd","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:05:21.764Z"}
