{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NMzmEvYhVBtWcgUCPQyrgj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→title: 'Multi-Stack Project Support'\n     3→slug: 'multi-stack-support'\n     4→created: '2026-03-23'\n     5→status: 'ready-for-dev'\n     6→stepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4]\n     7→tech_stack: ['typescript', 'vitest']\n     8→files_to_modify:\n     9→  - src/lib/stack-detect.ts\n    10→  - src/lib/otlp.ts\n    11→  - src/lib/coverage.ts\n    12→  - src/lib/state.ts\n    13→  - src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts\n    14→  - src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts\n    15→  - src/modules/infra/init-project.ts\n    16→  - src/commands/init.ts\n    17→  - src/templates/readme.ts\n    18→  - src/modules/infra/types.ts\n    19→  - src/modules/verify/env.ts\n    20→  - src/commands/teardown.ts\n    21→code_patterns:\n    22→  - 'stack: string | null → stacks: string[] throughout'\n    23→  - 'Primary stack = stacks[0] for backward compat'\n    24→  - 'Per-stack iteration for coverage, OTLP, docs'\n    25→test_patterns:\n    26→  - 'Multi-stack fixtures: dir with package.json + Cargo.toml'\n    27→  - 'Monorepo fixtures: frontend/package.json + backend/Cargo.toml'\n    28→  - 'Single-stack backward compat tests must not regress'\n    29→---\n    30→\n    31→# Tech-Spec: Multi-Stack Project Support\n    32→\n    33→**Created:** 2026-03-23\n    34→\n    35→## Overview\n    36→\n    37→### Problem Statement\n    38→\n    39→`detectStack()` returns a single `string | null`. Monorepo projects with `frontend/` (TS) + `backend/` (Rust) get only the first match. Coverage, OTLP, Dockerfile, and docs only target one stack. ~20 function signatures take `stack: string | null`. Projects with multiple stacks lose harness features for all stacks except the first detected.\n    40→\n    41→### Solution\n    42→\n    43→Change `detectStack()` to return `string[]` (array of all detected stacks). Each consumer iterates over stacks: coverage runs per-stack, OTLP installs per-stack, docs lists all stacks. Dockerfile uses a single multi-stage build. State stores `stacks: string[]` instead of `stack: string | null`. Add subdirectory scanning (1 level deep) for monorepo layout detection. Maintain backward compatibility via `stacks[0]` as primary stack.\n    44→\n    45→### Scope\n    46→\n    47→**In Scope:**\n    48→- `detectStack()` returns `string[]` with all detected stacks\n    49→- Subdirectory scanning for monorepo layouts (1 level deep)\n    50→- Per-stack coverage (run each stack's tool, report independently)\n    51→- Per-stack OTLP installation\n    52→- Combined docs scaffolding (list all stacks in AGENTS.md)\n    53→- Single Dockerfile with multi-stage build for all stacks\n    54→- State migration: `stack: string | null` → `stacks: string[]`\n    55→- Backward compat: primary stack = `stacks[0]` for consumers that need a single value\n    56→\n    57→**Out of Scope:**\n    58→- Deep nested monorepo scanning (only 1 level)\n    59→- Per-stack verification Dockerfiles (one combined)\n    60→- Workspace-level Cargo.toml detection within a TS monorepo\n    61→- Custom per-subdirectory config\n    62→\n    63→## Context for Development\n    64→\n    65→### Codebase Patterns\n    66→\n    67→- ~20 function signatures take `stack: string | null` — all need updating to `stacks: string[]` or providing a compat shim\n    68→- `HarnessState.stack` is persisted in YAML frontmatter — needs migration path\n    69→- All stack conditionals (`if stack === 'nodejs'`) become iteration (`for (const stack of stacks)`) or primary-stack access (`stacks[0]`)\n    70→- Tests use single-stack fixtures — need multi-stack variants added\n    71→\n    72→### Files to Reference\n    73→\n    74→| File | Purpose | Key Touchpoints |\n    75→| ---- | ------- | --------------- |\n    76→| `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` | `detectStack()` L7-14, `detectAppType()` L100 | Core: return `StackDetection[]` instead of `string \\| null`. Add `readdirSync` for subdir scan. `detectAppType()` signature stays — called per-stack. |\n    77→| `src/lib/state.ts` | `HarnessState` L7-41 | Add `stacks: string[]`, deprecate `stack: string \\| null`. Migration in `readState()`. |\n    78→| `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `detectCoverageTool()` L35-53, `runCoverage()` L194 | Callers pass single stack — no change to internal API. Init pipeline iterates stacks and calls per-stack. |\n    79→| `src/lib/otlp.ts` | `instrumentProject()` L345, `configureOtlpEnvVars()` L308 | Same — single-stack API. Init pipeline calls per-stack. |\n    80→| `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | `generateDockerfileTemplate()` L112 | New: `generateMultiStackDockerfile(stacks[])`. Composes per-stack build stages + combined runtime. |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cxxc3JMDGP4TtKB29uGny5","session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"bbe328a6-a36d-40d2-a702-5a34d467afa4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:09:27.732Z"}
