{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YYxvVbJ7fbVosLWSRGjpny","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Vu5YjMPguZX7EFaV13CUJr","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"STORY_CONTENT=$(cat /tmp/codeharness-verify-9-1-multi-stack-detection-subdir-scanning/story.md)\n\nPROMPT=\"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The src/ directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details. If you cannot verify a feature from docs + CLI alone, that is a REAL failure in the product's documentation or packaging.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading README.md in this workspace. It contains install and usage instructions for the project. Use it to understand how to exercise the CLI.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file story.md contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. Here is its content:\n\n---\n$STORY_CONTENT\n---\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion, you must:\n\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via docker exec codeharness-verify ...\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n4. For ACs that involve Claude Code sessions or agent workflows, use docker exec codeharness-verify claude ... to spawn real sessions inside the container\n\n### Docker Container\n\n- Container name: codeharness-verify\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: docker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n- Example: docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness --version\n- Example: docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness init --json\n\nThe container has the following tools installed:\n- codeharness — the project CLI\n- claude — Claude Code CLI (authenticated via ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var)\n- curl, jq — for querying observability endpoints\n- showboat — for proof document validation\n- node, npm — Node.js runtime\n\n### Project Type: Node.js CLI\n\nExecute commands inside the container and capture stdout/stderr as evidence:\n- docker exec codeharness-verify <cli-command> [args]\n- Capture exit codes: docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c '<command>; echo \\\"EXIT:\\$?\\\"'\n- For Node.js projects, the built artifact is installed globally in the container.\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery these from the HOST (not inside the container) for runtime evidence:\n\n- **VictoriaLogs** (logs): http://localhost:9428\n  - Example: curl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&limit=10'\n- **VictoriaMetrics** (metrics): http://localhost:8428\n  - Example: curl 'http://localhost:8428/api/v1/query?query=up'\n- **VictoriaTraces** (traces): http://localhost:16686\n  - Example: curl 'http://localhost:16686/api/traces?service=codeharness-verify&limit=10'\n\n## Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command\n\nAfter EACH docker exec command you run, query the observability backend for log events from the last 30 seconds:\n\ncurl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'\n\n- If the response contains one or more log entries, the code path has observability coverage. Note the count in your proof.\n- If the response contains zero log entries, the code path is a silent gap. Include this tag in the AC section of your proof:\n  [OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: verification/9-1-multi-stack-detection-subdir-scanning-proof.md\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n## AC N: <description>\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n\\`\\`\\`output\n<actual output>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use bash and output as code fence languages.** Never use bare code fences without a language tag.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. **ALL commands MUST use docker exec codeharness-verify ...** — do NOT run commands directly on the host filesystem.\n2. **Do NOT attempt to access source code** — there is no src/ directory in this workspace.\n3. **Report REAL failures** — if a feature does not work via the CLI, report that as a verification failure. Do NOT fabricate passing evidence.\n4. **Every AC needs functional evidence** — reading docs alone is not evidence. You must execute commands and capture output.\n5. **Verify aggressively, escalate narrowly.** If an AC has 5 parts and you can verify 4, verify those 4 and escalate ONLY the specific part you cannot reach.\n6. **[ESCALATE] is ONLY for things that are genuinely impossible to automate** — physical hardware, paid external services, human visual judgment. Infrastructure problems are NOT valid escalation reasons.\n7. **Never switch to unit-testable verification.** If Docker verification doesn't work, report WHY as a [FAIL].\n\n## IMPORTANT: detectStacks is an internal library function\n\nThe ACs reference detectStacks() and detectStack() which are internal TypeScript functions, not CLI commands. To verify them in black-box mode, you need to run a Node.js script inside the container that imports from the installed codeharness package. Try:\n\ndocker exec codeharness-verify node -e \\\"const m = require('codeharness'); console.log(Object.keys(m))\\\"\n\nto discover what's exported. Then create test directories and call the functions. For example:\n\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'mkdir -p /tmp/test && cd /tmp/test && echo {} > package.json && node -e \\\"const {detectStacks} = require(\\\\\\\"codeharness\\\\\\\"); console.log(JSON.stringify(detectStacks(\\\\\\\"/tmp/test\\\\\\\")))\\\"'\n\nIf detectStacks is not exported from the package, that itself is a finding — report it as [FAIL] with details.\"\n\ncd /tmp/codeharness-verify-9-1-multi-stack-detection-subdir-scanning && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"$PROMPT\" 2>&1","description":"Run black-box verifier session for story 9-1","timeout":300000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":448,"cache_read_input_tokens":57558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":448},"output_tokens":57,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"803388cc-cac4-4dd5-b1ce-cd637346ce0c"}
