{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FMuFZ1UZM4vRSwq8aAEFWP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 6)\n     2→\n     3→### 9-1-multi-stack-detection-subdir-scanning — create-story (2026-03-23T14:05Z)\n     4→\n     5→None.\n     6→\n     7→### 9-1-multi-stack-detection-subdir-scanning — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:08Z)\n     8→\n     9→- **Observation:** Story technical notes suggested `vi.mock('node:fs')` but existing tests use real temp directories. Followed existing pattern for consistency.\n    10→- **Observation:** AC2 specifies return order `[nodejs/frontend, rust/backend]` but AC6 says alphabetical by dir name — which gives `[backend, frontend]`. Implementation follows AC6. Spec inconsistency in story file.\n    11→\n    12→### 9-1-multi-stack-detection-subdir-scanning — code-review (2026-03-23T14:12Z)\n    13→\n    14→- **HIGH (fixed):** `detectStack()` compat wrapper returned subdirectory stacks — broke root-only callers. Fixed to filter `.dir === '.'`.\n    15→- **HIGH (fixed):** SKIP_DIRS missing `.venv`, `venv`, `.tox`, `.mypy_cache`, `.cache` — false-positive Python detection from venvs.\n    16→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `stack` field typed as `string` instead of `StackName` union — lost type safety.\n    17→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Unused type import in test file.\n    18→- **LOW (not fixed):** `readdirSync` follows symlinks, no test for non-existent dir catch branch, `detectStack()` return type not narrowed to `StackName | null` (would require downstream changes).\n    19→- **Divergence from tech spec:** Tech spec says `detectStack()` returns `stacks[0]?.stack`, but review fix changed to filter root-only. Downstream stories 9-2 through 9-5 need to be aware.\n    20→\n    21→### 9-1-multi-stack-detection-subdir-scanning — verification (2026-03-23T14:15Z)\n    22→\n    23→- All 6 ACs passed. Verifier used extracted function implementations from dist bundle since `detectStacks`/`detectStack` are not exported from the package.\n    24→- **Finding:** `detectStacks` and `detectStack` are NOT exported from the codeharness npm package — only `createProgram` and `parseStreamLine` are. Limits programmatic reuse by downstream consumers. May need to be addressed in story 9-2 or 9-3.\n    25→- **OBSERVABILITY GAP on all 6 ACs:** No log events detected. `detectStacks()` is a pure filesystem function with no telemetry — expected for utility functions.\n    26→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MMuf4b7jRDkQhB3HyTW1f7","session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"3641235f-0f41-499d-a375-760db6c0d2ce","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:18:29.712Z"}
