{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CY8fEjNb5fmz4Qqyeyv72M","type":"tool_result","content":"   100→\n   101→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   102→- [ ] Fix Docker container naming: align `codeharness status --check-docker` detection with `codeharness-shared-*` naming convention, or vice versa\n   103→- [ ] Add `rust_env_hint` field to init-time telemetry so VictoriaLogs captures Rust project setup events (observability gap)\n   104→- [ ] Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping into a single utility function (duplicated in docs-scaffold.ts and state.ts)\n   105→- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates instead of mapping them to `generic`\n   106→\n   107→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   108→- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (carried 9+ epics)\n   109→- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   110→- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   111→- [ ] Write integration test for `detectStack` -> `detectAppType` end-to-end flow\n   112→- [ ] Implement `tarpaulin-json` parser in `parseCoverageReport` (story 8-3 scope)\n   113→\n   114→---\n   115→\n   116→# Session Retrospective (Addendum) — 2026-03-23T09:50Z\n   117→\n   118→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint (Epic 8: Full Rust Stack Support)\n   119→**Session window:** ~09:08 - 09:50 UTC+4 (~42 minutes total, 3 Ralph iterations)\n   120→**Commits produced:** 3 (stories 8-1, 8-2) + 8-3 code review completed\n   121→**Sprint progress:** 27/34 stories done, 8-3 at `verifying` in sprint-status / `review` in sprint-state.json\n   122→\n   123→---\n   124→\n   125→## 1. Session Summary\n   126→\n   127→| Story | Phase Reached | Outcome | Notes |\n   128→|-------|--------------|---------|-------|\n   129→| 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection | done | Completed | Rust stack detection via Cargo.toml, app type inference. Commit `4c7f498`. |\n   130→| 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust | done | Completed | State types expanded for Rust. AC2 failed first pass (missing `rust_env_hint`), fixed in `9ddd65e`, verified in `d6a76bf`. |\n   131→| 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection | code-review done, verification not started | Incomplete | Story created, implemented, reviewed. HIGH bug found and fixed during review. Ran out of time before verification. |\n   132→\n   133→Three stories attempted across 3 Ralph iterations. Two completed (Epic 8.1 done). One (8-3) reached code review but not verification -- left in limbo between `verifying` (sprint-status.yaml) and `review` (sprint-state.json).\n   134→\n   135→Iteration 1 timed out at 30 minutes while writing the first retro. Iteration 2 completed 8-2 verification. Iteration 3 created, implemented, and reviewed 8-3 but hit the session wall before verification could run.\n   136→\n   137→---\n   138→\n   139→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   140→\n   141→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n   142→\n   143→| Severity | Story | Issue | Status |\n   144→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   145→| HIGH | 8-3 | `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. | Fixed -- global regex + aggregation loop |\n   146→| HIGH | 8-1 | `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps | Fixed -- `getCargoDepsSection()` |\n   147→| HIGH | 8-1 | Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`) | Fixed -- `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex |\n   148→| HIGH | 8-2 | `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack | Fixed |\n   149→| LOW | 8-3 | No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` -- string `\"85.5\"` vs number `85.5` | Not fixed, low risk |\n   150→| LOW | 8-3 | `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust -- unnecessary side effect in check-only mode | Not fixed, pre-existing pattern |\n   151→\n   152→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced This Session\n   153→\n   154→1. **ESM mocking workaround for 8-3:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', ...)` with file-level mock and `mockReset()` in `afterEach`. Applies to all tests in the file -- fragile if new tests are added without understanding the mock scope.\n   155→2. **Cargo test regex ordering is load-bearing:** The cargo test regex must appear before pytest regex because pytest's pattern false-matches on cargo test output. No guard comment or test enforcing this ordering.\n   156→3. **`coverage.ts` now exceeds 600 lines** (architecture limit is 300). Explicitly deferred splitting -- tracked but growing.\n   157→4. **Cargo.toml parsing remains string-based** (no TOML parser). `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection style unhandled.\n   158→5. **Duplicate stack-to-coverage-tool mapping** in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts`. No single source of truth.\n   159→\n   160→### Verification Gaps\n   161→\n   162→- **8-3 not verified.** Code review passed, but no verification run executed. Story left in inconsistent state across tracking files.\n   163→- **Branch coverage below floor.** `coverage.ts` branch coverage at 77.98% (below 80% floor). Caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n   164→- **No integration test for `cargo tarpaulin` execution.** All 8-3 tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing pattern but means actual tarpaulin output parsing is untested against real output.\n   165→\n   166→### Tooling / Infrastructure Problems\n   167→\n   168→- **Leftover Docker container** (`codeharness-verify`) from previous session required manual cleanup.\n   169→- **Docker naming mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` looks for different container names than `codeharness-shared-*` naming used by shared stack. Causes false \"stack down\" and port conflicts.\n   170→- **Observability gap:** `codeharness init` emits no log events to VictoriaLogs. Silent code path during verification.\n   171→- **`codeharness sync` broken:** Cannot find story Status line in story files. Pattern mismatch on `## Status:`. Broken for 9+ epics.\n   172→- **Ralph timeout:** Iteration 1 killed at 30 minutes mid-retro-write. Work lost, had to be regenerated.\n   173→- **State tracking desync:** `sprint-status.yaml` shows 8-3 as `verifying`, `sprint-state.json` shows `review`. No reconciliation mechanism.\n   174→\n   175→---\n   176→\n   177→## 3. What Went Well\n   178→\n   179→- **Three stories progressed in ~42 minutes.** Two fully completed (Epic 8.1 done), one through code review. Good velocity for Rust support work.\n   180→- **Code review caught a HIGH bug in 8-3** (`parseTestCounts` single-line capture for workspace projects) before it shipped. Self-review continues to be the highest-ROI quality gate.\n   181→- **10 bugs found and fixed across 8-1 and 8-2** during implementation, before verification even ran. The implementation subagent's review pass is consistently effective.\n   182→- **97% test coverage on 8-1.** All 123 files above 80% floor.\n   183→- **Clean commit history.** Feature, fix, and verification commits clearly scoped and traceable.\n   184→\n   185→---\n   186→\n   187→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   188→\n   189→- **8-3 incomplete.** Ran out of session budget before verification. The story is in a split-brain state between tracking files.\n   190→- **Ralph iteration 1 timeout.** 30-minute window insufficient for 2 stories + retro. The retro was being written when killed -- wasted token spend on a partial file that had to be regenerated.\n   191→- **Docker infrastructure friction.** Container naming mismatch and leftover containers wasted verification time on both 8-2 and would have affected 8-3.\n   192→- **`codeharness sync` still broken.** Story file statuses stuck at `ready-for-dev`. This has been a known issue for 9+ epics with no fix. It creates noise in every session.\n   193→- **Branch coverage degradation.** `coverage.ts` dropped below 80% branch coverage floor. Not caused by this session's changes, but the file is growing (600+ lines) and the gap will widen as more Rust code is added.\n   194→\n   195→---\n   196→\n   197→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   198→\n   199→### Repeat"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MMuf4b7jRDkQhB3HyTW1f7","session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"9c228d11-bb45-4e29-935d-d17be9d9d077","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:18:52.215Z"}
