{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ruxo2HnZJ34uRwpSXTm1Nr","type":"tool_result","content":"   199→### Repeat\n   200→- **Self-review before verification.** Found 10 bugs in 8-1/8-2 and 1 HIGH bug in 8-3 during code review. This pattern is the single most effective quality measure in the pipeline.\n   201→- **Separate fix commits from feature commits.** Clean git history makes debugging verification failures straightforward.\n   202→- **Track issues in `.session-issues.md` as they happen.** Having the raw materials for the retro available made this addendum possible even after iteration timeout.\n   203→\n   204→### Avoid\n   205→- **Do not schedule retro writing inside the same iteration budget as implementation.** Iteration 1 timed out writing the retro. The retro should be a dedicated, short iteration or run outside Ralph.\n   206→- **Do not trust `codeharness status --check-docker`.** Docker naming mismatch makes the output unreliable. Verify containers manually with `docker ps`.\n   207→- **Do not let `coverage.ts` grow further without splitting.** It is 2x the architecture limit and branch coverage is degrading. Next story touching this file should refactor.\n   208→\n   209→---\n   210→\n   211→## 6. Action Items\n   212→\n   213→### Fix Now (before next session)\n   214→- [ ] Reconcile 8-3 state: set consistent status across `sprint-status.yaml` and `sprint-state.json` (currently `verifying` vs `review`)\n   215→- [ ] Run 8-3 verification to complete the story\n   216→- [ ] Clean up leftover Docker containers\n   217→\n   218→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   219→- [ ] Split `coverage.ts` into separate modules (Rust, Node, Python parsers). File is 600+ lines, 2x the 300-line architecture limit.\n   220→- [ ] Fix Docker container naming alignment between `codeharness status --check-docker` and `codeharness-shared-*` convention\n   221→- [ ] Add guard comment or ordering test for the cargo-test/pytest regex precedence in coverage parsing\n   222→- [ ] Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping into a single utility function\n   223→- [ ] Add `rust_env_hint` to init-time telemetry (observability gap)\n   224→\n   225→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   226→- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (broken 9+ epics, creating noise every session)\n   227→- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   228→- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   229→- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates\n   230→- [ ] Add type validation to `parseTarpaulinCoverage` for string vs number coverage values\n   231→- [ ] Write integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` output parsing (not just mocked)\n   232→\n   233→---\n   234→\n   235→# Session Retrospective (Final) -- 2026-03-23T10:30Z\n   236→\n   237→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint (Epic 8: Full Rust Stack Support)\n   238→**Full session window:** ~09:08 - 10:30 UTC+4 (~82 minutes total, 4 Ralph iterations)\n   239→**Commits produced:** 3 (stories 8-1, 8-2)\n   240→**Sprint progress:** 28/34 stories done, 6 remaining in backlog (all Epic 8.2-8.5)\n   241→\n   242→This is the final consolidated retrospective for the 2026-03-23 session. Two prior addenda covered iterations 1-3. This covers iteration 4 (8-3 verification) and provides a full-session analysis.\n   243→\n   244→---\n   245→\n   246→## 1. Session Summary\n   247→\n   248→| Story | Phase | Outcome | Iterations | Notes |\n   249→|-------|-------|---------|------------|-------|\n   250→| 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection | done | Completed | 1 | Rust stack detection via Cargo.toml. Commit `4c7f498`. |\n   251→| 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust | done | Completed | 1-2 | State types for Rust. AC2 failed first pass, fixed in `9ddd65e`, verified in `d6a76bf`. |\n   252→| 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection | done | Completed | 3-4 | Created, implemented, reviewed in iteration 3. Verified in iteration 4 via Docker black-box. |\n   253→\n   254→Three stories attempted, three completed. Epic 8.1 (Rust Detection Foundation) and the first story of Epic 8.2 (Rust Coverage & Testing) are done. Session ended with NO_WORK -- all remaining Epic 8 stories (8-4 through 8-9) are in backlog and require explicit promotion to be picked up.\n   255→\n   256→### Iteration Timeline\n   257→\n   258→| Iteration | Duration | Work Done | Outcome |\n   259→|-----------|----------|-----------|---------|\n   260→| 1 | 30 min (timeout) | 8-1 impl+verify, 8-2 impl+verify | Timed out mid-retrospective write |\n   261→| 2 | ~8 min | 8-2 verification commit, retro written | Completed |\n   262→| 3 | ~12 min | 8-3 create-story, dev-story, code-review | Completed (verification deferred) |\n   263→| 4 | ~20 min | 8-3 Docker black-box verification | Completed, story marked done |\n   264→\n   265→---\n   266→\n   267→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   268→\n   269→### Bugs Discovered and Fixed (4 HIGH, 6 MEDIUM)\n   270→\n   271→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n   272→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   273→| HIGH | 8-3 | `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line -- workspace projects emit one per crate | Yes -- global regex + aggregation loop |\n   274→| HIGH | 8-1 | `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps | Yes -- `getCargoDepsSection()` |\n   275→| HIGH | 8-1 | Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`) | Yes -- `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex |\n   276→| HIGH | 8-2 | `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack | Yes |\n   277→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | `[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside TOML comments | Yes -- line-anchored regexes |\n   278→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | Missing test coverage for 3 of 5 web frameworks | Yes -- tests added |\n   279→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch | Yes |\n   280→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` | Yes |\n   281→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch | Yes |\n   282→| MEDIUM | 8-3 | AGENTS.md stale for coverage module (missing cargo-tarpaulin) | Yes |\n   283→\n   284→### Known Issues NOT Fixed (accepted risk)\n   285→\n   286→| Severity | Story | Issue | Reason |\n   287→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   288→| LOW | 8-3 | No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` (string vs number) | Low risk, `?? 0` handles `undefined` |\n   289→| LOW | 8-3 | `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` in check-only mode | Pre-existing pattern across all stacks |\n   290→| LOW | 8-1 | `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML | Accepted per NFR4 (no TOML parser dep) |\n   291→| LOW | 8-2 | Duplicate stack-to-tool mapping in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts` | Tech debt tracked |\n   292→\n   293→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced\n   294→\n   295→1. **ESM mocking workaround:** `vi.mock('node:child_process', ...)` with file-level mock and `mockReset()` in `afterEach`. Cannot use `vi.spyOn` on `execSync` in ESM mode. Fragile if new tests are added without understanding mock scope.\n   296→2. **Cargo test regex ordering is load-bearing:** Must appear before pytest regex to avoid false matches. No guard comment or ordering test.\n   297→3. **`coverage.ts` now exceeds 600 lines** (architecture limit is 300). Deliberately deferred splitting.\n   298→4. **Cargo.toml parsing is string-based** (no TOML parser). Edge cases with inline subsections and comments remain.\n   299→\n   300→### Verification Gaps\n   301→\n   302→- **8-3 AC1/AC2 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `codeharness coverage --json` does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` fields. The verifier had to replicate `detectCoverageTool()` logic from `dist/index.js` to confirm output. This is a CLI/API gap -- internal functions are not fully exercisable through the CLI.\n   303→- **8-3 AC4 verified via function replication.** `parseTestCounts` is internal with no CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output.\n   304→- **Branch coverage at 77.98%** on `coverage.ts` (below 80% floor). Pre-existing untested branches, not caused by new code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n   305→- **No observability data during verification.** VictoriaLogs received no events during any verification run. Docker container lacks Docker-in-Docker, and `codeharness init` does not emit structured telemetry.\n   306→\n   307→### Tooling / Infrastructure Problems\n   308→\n   309→| Problem | Impact | Recurring? |\n   310→|---------|--------|------------|\n   311→| Leftover `codeharness-verify` container from previous session | Wasted cleanup time at start of verification | Yes (3rd session in a row) |\n   312→| Docker naming mismatch (`codeharness-shared-*` vs compose names) | False \"stack down\" reports, port conflicts | Yes (known since Epic 7) |\n   313→| `codeharness sync` broken (can't find Status line in story files) | Story file statuses stuck at `ready-for-dev` | Yes (broken 9+ epics) |\n   314→| Ralph iteration 1 timed out at 30 min | Lost retro work, required regeneration | First occurrence with 2-story load |\n   315→| State tracking desync between `sprint-status.yaml` and `sprint-state.json` | Ambiguous story status between files | Yes (every session) |\n   316→\n   317→---\n   318→\n   319→## 3. What Went Well\n   320→\n   321→- **Three stories completed in a single session.** Epic 8.1 fully done. First story of Epic 8.2 done. Sprint progress moved from 25/34 to 28/34.\n   322→- **Self-review caught 10 bugs before verification.** The pattern of implementation followed by code review before verification continues to be the highest-ROI quality gate. The HIGH bug in `parseTestCounts` (workspace aggregation) would have been a runtime defect.\n   323→- **97% test coverage on 8-1.** All 123 files above 80% floor. 2980 tests passing, zero regressions.\n   324→- **Session issues log worked as designed.** Each subagent appended real issues as they encountered them. This file was the raw material for all three retrospective addenda.\n   325→- **Docker verification for 8-3 succeeded on first attempt** in iteration 4, despite the story being complex (internal functions not directly CLI-exercisable).\n   326→\n   327→---\n   328→\n   329→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   330→\n   331→- **Iteration 1 timeout.** 30-minute budget was insufficient for implementing, verifying, and retro-writing two stories. The retro was killed mid-write, wasting tokens and requiring regeneration.\n   332→- **8-2 AC2 failed first verification pass.** `rust_env_hint` was missed in the initial implementation. Required a separate fix commit and re-verify cycle.\n   333→- **8-3 verification deferred across iterations.** Code review completed in iteration 3 but verification didn't run until iteration 4. The story spent ~40 minutes in limbo between `verifying` and `review` status across different tracking files.\n   334→- **Docker infrastructure friction consumed time in every iteration.** Container naming mismatch, leftover containers, and port conflicts are recurring problems that have not been fixed.\n   335→- **`codeharness sync` is still broken.** This has been a known issue for 9+ epics. Story file statuses are permanently stuck at `ready-for-dev`. At this point it's actively harmful -- it creates noise in every session and gives false confidence to anyone reading story files.\n   336→\n   337→---\n   338→\n   339→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   340→\n   341→### Repeat\n   342→\n   343→- **Self-review before verification.** Found 10 bugs across 3 stories before any verification run. This is consistently the best quality investment.\n   344→- **Track issues in `.session-issues.md` as they happen.** Having timestamped raw materials made retrospectives possible even after iteration timeouts.\n   345→- **Separate fix commits from feature commits.** Clean git history makes debugging straightforward.\n   346→- **Session retro addenda pattern works.** Appending to the retro file after each iteration gives progressive visibility without losing earlier analysis.\n   347→\n   348→### Avoid\n   349→\n   350→- **Do not schedule retro writing inside the same iteration budget as implementation.** Iteration 1 proved this -- the retro was killed mid-write. Retros should be a dedicated short iteration or run outside Ralph.\n   351→- **Do not trust `codeharness status --check-docker`.** Docker naming mismatch makes output unreliable. Use `docker ps` directly.\n   352→- **Do not let `coverage.ts` grow further without splitting.** It is 2x the architecture limit (600+ lines vs 300) and branch coverage is degrading. The next story touching this file must split it.\n   353→- **Do not defer fixing recurring infrastructure issues.** Docker naming mismatch and `codeharness sync` breakage have been noted in retrospectives for 9+ epics. Each session wastes time on the same workarounds.\n   354→\n   355→---\n   356→\n   357→## 6. Action Items\n   358→\n   359→### Fix Now (before next session)\n   360→\n   361→- [ ] Reconcile `sprint-state.json` -- set 8-3 status to `done` to match `sprint-status.yaml`\n   362→- [ ] Clean up leftover Docker containers (`codeharness-verify`, duplicates)\n   363→- [ ] Verify `state-snapshot.json` has 8-2 and 8-3 both as `done`\n   364→\n   365→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   366→\n   367→- [ ] **Split `coverage.ts`** into separate modules (Rust, Node, Python parsers). 600+ lines, 2x the 300-line limit. Branch coverage already degrading.\n   368→- [ ] **Fix Docker container naming** -- align `codeharness status --check-docker` with `codeharness-shared-*` convention. This has wasted time every session since Epic 7.\n   369→- [ ] **Add guard comment or ordering test** for cargo-test/pytest regex precedence in coverage parsing\n   370→- [ ] **Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping** into a single utility function (duplicated in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts`)\n   371→- [ ] **Add `rust_env_hint` to init-time telemetry** (observability gap -- no VictoriaLogs events during Rust project init)\n   372→- [ ] **Expose `runCommand` and `reportFormat` in CLI JSON output** -- `codeharness coverage --json` currently omits these fields, forcing verification to replicate internal function logic\n   373→\n   374→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   375→\n   376→- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (broken 9+ epics, noted in every retro)\n   377→- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   378→- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   379→- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates instead of mapping to `generic`\n   380→- [ ] Add type validation to `parseTarpaulinCoverage` for string vs number coverage values\n   381→- [ ] Write integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` output parsing (not just mocked)\n   382→- [ ] Add `parseTestCounts` CLI subcommand for direct test output parsing (currently internal-only)\n   383→\n   384→---\n   385→\n   386→## Session Metrics\n   387→\n   388→| Metric | Value |\n   389→|--------|-------|\n   390→| Stories completed | 3 (8-1, 8-2, 8-3) |\n   391→| Stories failed | 0 |\n   392→| Bugs found pre-verification | 10 (4 HIGH, 6 MEDIUM) |\n   393→| Bugs shipped unfixed | 0 HIGH/MEDIUM, 4 LOW (accepted) |\n   394→| Ralph iterations | 4 |\n   395→| Timeouts | 1 (iteration 1) |\n   396→| Commits | 3 |\n   397→| Tests added | ~25 new tests |\n   398→| Total test count | 2980 passing |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MMuf4b7jRDkQhB3HyTW1f7","session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"4c426fb9-dd78-4007-bba2-e5b2c2ee8fc3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:18:55.748Z"}
