{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DWD24FKB1TwaR3NMHZCD8E","type":"tool_result","content":"   398→| Total test count | 2980 passing |\n   399→| Sprint progress | 25/34 -> 28/34 (82% done) |\n   400→| Remaining backlog | 6 stories (Epic 8.2-8.5) |\n   401→\n   402→---\n   403→\n   404→# Session Retrospective (Continued) -- 2026-03-23T14:30Z\n   405→\n   406→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint (Epic 8: Full Rust Stack Support)\n   407→**Full session window:** ~09:08 - 10:40 UTC+4 (~92 minutes total, 5 Ralph iterations)\n   408→**Commits produced:** 4 (stories 8-1, 8-2, 8-3, 8-4)\n   409→**Sprint progress:** 29/34 stories done per sprint-status.yaml, 5 remaining in backlog (all Epic 8.3-8.5)\n   410→\n   411→This addendum covers iteration 5 (story 8-4) and provides a consolidated session-end analysis incorporating all issues from `.session-issues.md`.\n   412→\n   413→---\n   414→\n   415→## 1. Session Summary\n   416→\n   417→| Story | Phase | Outcome | Iteration(s) | Commit |\n   418→|-------|-------|---------|---------------|--------|\n   419→| 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection | done | Completed | 1 | `4c7f498` |\n   420→| 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust | done | Completed | 1-2 | `9ddd65e`, `d6a76bf` |\n   421→| 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection | done | Completed | 3-4 | `ebaddac` |\n   422→| 8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry | done (sprint-status) / review (sprint-state) | Completed with state desync | 5 | `4e805b9` |\n   423→\n   424→Four stories completed across 5 Ralph iterations. Epic 8.1 (Rust Detection Foundation) fully done. Epic 8.2 (Rust Coverage & Testing) fully done. Sprint moved from 25/34 to 29/34 (85%).\n   425→\n   426→### Iteration Timeline\n   427→\n   428→| Iteration | Duration | Work Done | Outcome |\n   429→|-----------|----------|-----------|---------|\n   430→| 1 | 30 min (timeout) | 8-1 impl+verify, 8-2 impl+verify | Timed out mid-retrospective write |\n   431→| 2 | ~8 min | 8-2 verification commit, retro written | Completed |\n   432→| 3 | ~12 min | 8-3 create-story, dev-story, code-review | Completed (verification deferred) |\n   433→| 4 | ~20 min | 8-3 Docker black-box verification | Completed, story marked done |\n   434→| 5 | ~15 min | 8-4 create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | Completed, all 5 ACs passed |\n   435→\n   436→---\n   437→\n   438→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   439→\n   440→### Bugs Discovered and Fixed (5 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM)\n   441→\n   442→| Severity | Story | Issue | Status |\n   443→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   444→| HIGH | 8-3 | `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line -- workspace projects emit one per crate | Fixed -- global regex + aggregation loop |\n   445→| HIGH | 8-1 | `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps | Fixed -- `getCargoDepsSection()` |\n   446→| HIGH | 8-1 | Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`) | Fixed -- `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex |\n   447→| HIGH | 8-2 | `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack | Fixed |\n   448→| HIGH | 8-4 (pre-existing) | 4 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts` when run as full suite -- test isolation issue | Not fixed, pre-existing |\n   449→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | `[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside TOML comments | Fixed -- line-anchored regexes |\n   450→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | Missing test coverage for 3 of 5 web frameworks | Fixed -- tests added |\n   451→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch | Fixed |\n   452→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` | Fixed |\n   453→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch | Fixed |\n   454→| MEDIUM | 8-4 | AGENTS.md stale -- deps.ts description omitted cargo-tarpaulin from tool list | Fixed |\n   455→| MEDIUM | 8-4 | Story File List empty -- no files documented in Dev Agent Record | Fixed |\n   456→\n   457→### Known Issues NOT Fixed (accepted risk)\n   458→\n   459→| Severity | Story | Issue | Reason |\n   460→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   461→| LOW | 8-3 | No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` (string vs number) | Low risk |\n   462→| LOW | 8-3 | `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` in check-only mode | Pre-existing pattern |\n   463→| LOW | 8-1 | `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML | Accepted per NFR4 |\n   464→| LOW | 8-2 | Duplicate stack-to-tool mapping in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts` | Tech debt tracked |\n   465→| LOW | 8-4 | Fragile catch-all mock in `installAllDependencies` tests -- handles cargo-tarpaulin via fallthrough | Accepted |\n   466→| LOW | 8-4 | Unconditional `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` on non-Rust projects -- noisy but graceful (`critical: false`) | Stack-conditional filtering deferred |\n   467→\n   468→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced This Session\n   469→\n   470→1. **ESM mocking workaround (8-3):** `vi.mock('node:child_process', ...)` with file-level mock and `mockReset()` in `afterEach`. Cannot use `vi.spyOn` on `execSync` in ESM mode.\n   471→2. **Cargo test regex ordering is load-bearing (8-3):** Must appear before pytest regex to avoid false matches. No guard comment or ordering test.\n   472→3. **`coverage.ts` exceeds 600 lines (8-3):** Architecture limit is 300. Deliberately deferred splitting. Branch coverage now at 77.98% (below 80% floor).\n   473→4. **Cargo.toml parsing is string-based (8-1):** No TOML parser per NFR4. Edge cases with `[dependencies.foo]` subsections remain.\n   474→5. **Unconditional dependency registry (8-4):** `cargo-tarpaulin` is installed on all projects regardless of stack. Fails gracefully but generates noise.\n   475→6. **Pre-existing test isolation failure (8-4):** 4 tests in `state.test.ts` fail in full-suite mode. Not addressed.\n   476→\n   477→### Verification Gaps\n   478→\n   479→- **8-3 AC1/AC2 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `codeharness coverage --json` does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` fields. Verifier replicated internal logic from `dist/index.js`.\n   480→- **8-3 AC4 verified via function replication.** `parseTestCounts` is internal with no CLI subcommand.\n   481→- **Branch coverage at 77.98%** on `coverage.ts` (below 80% floor). Pre-existing, not caused by new code.\n   482→- **No observability data during any verification.** VictoriaLogs received no events. Docker containers lack Docker-in-Docker.\n   483→- **8-4 showboat not installed.** `codeharness verify` warning about missing showboat. Non-blocking.\n   484→\n   485→### Tooling / Infrastructure Problems\n   486→\n   487→| Problem | Impact | Recurring? | Sessions affected |\n   488→|---------|--------|------------|-------------------|\n   489→| Leftover `codeharness-verify` container | Cleanup time at session start | Yes | 3+ sessions |\n   490→| Docker naming mismatch (`codeharness-shared-*` vs compose) | False \"stack down\", port conflicts | Yes | Since Epic 7 |\n   491→| `codeharness sync` broken (Status header pattern) | Story file statuses permanently stale | Yes | 9+ epics |\n   492→| Ralph iteration 1 timeout at 30 min | Lost retro work mid-write | Occasional | This session |\n   493→| State tracking desync (sprint-status vs sprint-state vs state-snapshot) | Ambiguous story status | Yes | Every session |\n   494→| `bd` binary not installed | Beads sync fails silently | Yes | 3+ sessions |\n   495→| Showboat not installed | No re-verification option | Yes | This session |\n   496→\n   497→### State Tracking Desync (Detailed)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MMuf4b7jRDkQhB3HyTW1f7","session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"704a4057-2be9-4b30-8216-b51a99d13190","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:19:00.238Z"}
