{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YH344vQYBdwmvBe66wh6F2","type":"tool_result","content":"   497→### State Tracking Desync (Detailed)\n   498→\n   499→This session ended with three tracking files disagreeing on 8-4 status:\n   500→- `sprint-status.yaml`: 8-4 = `done`\n   501→- `sprint-state.json`: 8-4 = `review` (should be `done`)\n   502→- `.state-snapshot.json`: 8-4 = `backlog` (stale, not updated by iteration 5)\n   503→\n   504→Similarly, `.state-snapshot.json` shows 8-3 as `verifying` and sprint done count as 27, while `sprint-state.json` shows 8-3 as `done` and count as 28. The snapshot file is clearly stale from an earlier iteration.\n   505→\n   506→---\n   507→\n   508→## 3. What Went Well\n   509→\n   510→- **Four stories completed in one session.** Epic 8.1 and Epic 8.2 both fully done. Sprint at 85% completion.\n   511→- **Self-review caught 12 bugs before verification.** 5 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM across 4 stories. The pattern of code-review before verification continues to be the single most effective quality gate.\n   512→- **8-4 completed cleanly.** All 5 ACs passed black-box verification on first attempt. 97% overall test coverage, all 123 files above 80% floor.\n   513→- **Session issues log worked as designed.** Every subagent appended issues as encountered. The log was the raw material for this and all prior retrospective addenda.\n   514→- **Progressive retro addenda pattern.** Each iteration produced or updated the retro, giving visibility even when iterations timed out.\n   515→\n   516→---\n   517→\n   518→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   519→\n   520→- **Iteration 1 timeout.** 30-minute budget was insufficient for 2 stories + retro. Retro killed mid-write, had to be regenerated in iteration 2.\n   521→- **State tracking is fundamentally broken.** Three files (`sprint-status.yaml`, `sprint-state.json`, `.state-snapshot.json`) all disagree on story statuses. No reconciliation mechanism exists. This has been true every session and is getting worse as more stories complete.\n   522→- **Docker infrastructure friction in every verification.** Container naming mismatch, leftover containers, and port conflicts are recurring costs. Noted in retros since Epic 7 with no fix.\n   523→- **`codeharness sync` has been broken for 9+ epics.** Every retro since Epic 0 mentions this. At this point the feature is non-functional and actively wastes attention.\n   524→- **8-4 dependency registry is unconditional.** `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` runs on Node.js and Python projects. Graceful failure, but noisy and wasteful.\n   525→- **Pre-existing test isolation failures.** 4 tests in `state.test.ts` fail in full-suite mode. Carried forward without fix.\n   526→\n   527→---\n   528→\n   529→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   530→\n   531→### Repeat\n   532→\n   533→- **Self-review before verification.** 12 bugs found across 4 stories. This is consistently the highest-ROI quality investment. Do not skip it.\n   534→- **Track issues in `.session-issues.md` in real time.** Timestamped raw materials made all retro addenda possible, even after timeouts.\n   535→- **Separate fix commits from feature commits.** Git history stays clean and debugging verification failures is straightforward.\n   536→- **Progressive retro addenda.** Appending after each significant iteration gives incremental visibility without blocking on a final pass.\n   537→\n   538→### Avoid\n   539→\n   540→- **Do not rely on state file consistency.** Three tracking files (`sprint-status.yaml`, `sprint-state.json`, `.state-snapshot.json`) diverge every session. Treat `sprint-status.yaml` as source of truth; treat the others as stale caches.\n   541→- **Do not defer Docker naming fix any longer.** This is the 5th+ retro noting the same problem. The workaround cost compounds every session.\n   542→- **Do not add to `coverage.ts` without splitting first.** At 600+ lines (2x the 300-line limit) with branch coverage below floor, the file is a maintenance liability. Next story touching it must refactor.\n   543→- **Do not schedule retrospective inside the same timeout as implementation.** Budget retro writing as a separate, short iteration.\n   544→\n   545→---\n   546→\n   547→## 6. Action Items\n   548→\n   549→### Fix Now (before next session)\n   550→\n   551→- [ ] Reconcile `sprint-state.json` -- set 8-4 status to `done` to match `sprint-status.yaml`\n   552→- [ ] Reconcile `.state-snapshot.json` -- update 8-3 to `done`, 8-4 to `done`, sprint done count to 29\n   553→- [ ] Clean up leftover Docker containers (`codeharness-verify`, duplicates)\n   554→\n   555→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   556→\n   557→- [ ] **Split `coverage.ts`** into Rust/Node/Python parser modules. 600+ lines, 2x the 300-line limit, branch coverage degrading.\n   558→- [ ] **Fix Docker container naming** -- align `codeharness status --check-docker` with `codeharness-shared-*`. Wasting time every session since Epic 7.\n   559→- [ ] **Add stack-conditional filtering to dependency registry** -- `cargo-tarpaulin` should only install for Rust projects.\n   560→- [ ] **Add guard comment or ordering test** for cargo-test/pytest regex precedence.\n   561→- [ ] **Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping** into single utility (duplicated in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `state.ts`).\n   562→- [ ] **Expose `runCommand` and `reportFormat` in `codeharness coverage --json`** -- internal fields not accessible via CLI, forcing verification to replicate logic.\n   563→- [ ] **Add `rust_env_hint` to init-time telemetry** -- observability gap, no VictoriaLogs events during Rust init.\n   564→- [ ] **Fix 4 pre-existing test isolation failures** in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts`.\n   565→\n   566→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   567→\n   568→- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (broken 9+ epics, noted in every retro)\n   569→- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   570→- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   571→- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates\n   572→- [ ] Add type validation to `parseTarpaulinCoverage` for string vs number values\n   573→- [ ] Write integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` output parsing (not just mocked)\n   574→- [ ] Add `parseTestCounts` CLI subcommand for direct test output parsing\n   575→- [ ] Install `bd` binary so beads sync can function\n   576→- [ ] Install showboat for re-verification capability\n   577→\n   578→---\n   579→\n   580→## Session Metrics (Final)\n   581→\n   582→| Metric | Value |\n   583→|--------|-------|\n   584→| Stories completed | 4 (8-1, 8-2, 8-3, 8-4) |\n   585→| Stories failed | 0 |\n   586→| Bugs found pre-verification | 12 (5 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM) |\n   587→| Bugs shipped unfixed | 0 HIGH/MEDIUM, 6 LOW (accepted) |\n   588→| Ralph iterations | 5 |\n   589→| Timeouts | 1 (iteration 1) |\n   590→| Commits | 4 |\n   591→| Total test count | 2980+ passing |\n   592→| Sprint progress | 25/34 -> 29/34 (85% done) |\n   593→| Epics completed this session | 2 (Epic 8.1, Epic 8.2) |\n   594→| Remaining backlog | 5 stories (Epic 8.3-8.5) |\n   595→| Recurring issues unfixed | 5 (Docker naming, sync, state desync, test isolation, coverage.ts size) |\n   596→\n   597→---\n   598→\n   599→# Session Retrospective (Addendum 4) -- 2026-03-23T18:45Z\n   600→\n   601→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint (Epic 8: Full Rust Stack Support)\n   602→**Full session window:** ~09:08 - 11:00 UTC+4 (~112 minutes total, 6 Ralph iterations)\n   603→**Commits produced:** 5 (stories 8-1, 8-2, 8-3, 8-4, 8-5)\n   604→**Sprint progress:** 30/34 stories done per sprint-status.yaml, 4 remaining in backlog (Epic 8.3-8.5)\n   605→\n   606→This addendum covers iteration 6 (story 8-5: Rust Dockerfile Template) and provides the final consolidated session analysis.\n   607→\n   608→---\n   609→\n   610→## 1. Session Summary\n   611→\n   612→|