{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DufWXbPfth4nwSM2eYEiiS","type":"tool_result","content":"   696→\n   697→---\n   698→\n   699→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   700→\n   701→### Repeat\n   702→\n   703→- **Self-review before verification.** 14 bugs found across 5 stories this session. This is the single most effective quality measure. Never skip it.\n   704→- **Track issues in `.session-issues.md` in real time.** Every subagent appended issues as encountered. This file made 4 retrospective addenda possible.\n   705→- **One story per iteration after the first.** Iterations 5 and 6 each completed a full story lifecycle in 15-20 minutes. This pacing works reliably.\n   706→- **Follow existing patterns for new stack support.** 8-5 had zero workarounds because it followed the established template pattern exactly.\n   707→\n   708→### Avoid\n   709→\n   710→- **Do not pack more than 1 story + retro into a 30-minute iteration.** Iteration 1 proved this. Budget 1 story per iteration, retro as a separate short iteration.\n   711→- **Do not defer `coverage.ts` split any further.** It has been flagged in 3 consecutive story reviews. Story 8-6 or 8-7 will add more Rust code to it. Split before continuing.\n   712→- **Do not ignore the state tracking desync.** Three files disagreeing on story status is not \"eventually consistent\" -- it is broken. Pick one source of truth and deprecate or automate the others.\n   713→\n   714→---\n   715→\n   716→## 6. Action Items\n   717→\n   718→### Fix Now (before next session)\n   719→\n   720→- [ ] Reconcile all three state files (`sprint-status.yaml`, `sprint-state.json`, `.state-snapshot.json`) -- set 8-5 to `done`, sprint done count to 30\n   721→- [ ] Clean up leftover Docker containers\n   722→\n   723→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   724→\n   725→- [ ] **Split `coverage.ts`** into Rust/Node/Python parser modules. 600+ lines, 2x the 300-line limit. Branch coverage below floor. Blocking further growth.\n   726→- [ ] **Fix Docker container naming** -- align detection with `codeharness-shared-*`. Wastes time every session since Epic 7.\n   727→- [ ] **Add stack-conditional filtering to dependency registry** -- `cargo-tarpaulin` should only install for Rust projects.\n   728→- [ ] **Add guard comment or ordering test** for cargo-test/pytest regex precedence.\n   729→- [ ] **Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping** into single utility.\n   730→- [ ] **Expose `runCommand`/`reportFormat` in `codeharness coverage --json`** -- CLI gap forces verification to replicate internal logic.\n   731→- [ ] **Add `rust_env_hint` to init-time telemetry** -- observability gap.\n   732→- [ ] **Fix 4 pre-existing test isolation failures** in `state.test.ts`.\n   733→- [ ] **Fix 1 pre-existing failure** in `migration.test.ts`.\n   734→\n   735→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   736→\n   737→- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (broken 9+ epics)\n   738→- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   739→- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   740→- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates\n   741→- [ ] Add type validation to `parseTarpaulinCoverage` for string vs number values\n   742→- [ ] Write integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` output parsing\n   743→- [ ] Add `parseTestCounts` CLI subcommand for direct test output parsing\n   744→- [ ] Install `bd` binary so beads sync can function\n   745→- [ ] Install showboat for re-verification capability\n   746→- [ ] Add ENTRYPOINT/CMD to Rust Dockerfile template (or document why it is omitted)\n   747→- [ ] Add error-path tests for non-nodejs stacks in dockerfile-template\n   748→\n   749→---\n   750→\n   751→## Session Metrics (Final -- Addendum 4)\n   752→\n   753→| Metric | Value |\n   754→|--------|-------|\n   755→| Stories completed | 5 (8-1, 8-2, 8-3, 8-4, 8-5) |\n   756→| Stories failed | 0 |\n   757→| Bugs found pre-verification | 14 (5 HIGH, 9 MEDIUM) |\n   758→| Bugs shipped unfixed | 0 HIGH/MEDIUM, 7 LOW (accepted) |\n   759→| Ralph iterations | 6 |\n   760→| Timeouts | 1 (iteration 1) |\n   761→| Commits | 5 |\n   762→| Total test count | 2994+ passing (2995 total, 1 pre-existing failure) |\n   763→| Sprint progress | 25/34 -> 30/34 (88% done) |\n   764→| Epics completed this session | 2 full (Epic 8.1, 8.2) + 1 partial (Epic 8.3: 1/2 stories) |\n   765→| Remaining backlog | 4 stories (8-6, 8-7, 8-8, 8-9 in Epic 8.3-8.5) |\n   766→| Recurring issues unfixed | 8 (Docker naming, sync, state desync, test isolation, coverage.ts size, migration test, bd, showboat) |\n   767→| Session velocity | ~5 stories / ~112 min = 1 story per ~22 min avg |\n   768→\n   769→---\n   770→\n   771→# Addendum 5 — Story 8-6 Completion (2026-03-23T11:30Z)\n   772→\n   773→**Session window:** ~11:07 - 11:30 UTC (Ralph iteration 7)\n   774→**Commits produced:** 1 (`f33294b`)\n   775→\n   776→---\n   777→\n   778→## 1. Session Summary\n   779→\n   780→| Story | Outcome | Commit | Notes |\n   781→|-------|---------|--------|-------|\n   782→| 8-6-rust-verification-dockerfile | done | `f33294b` | Full lifecycle: create-story, dev, code-review, verify |\n   783→\n   784→One story attempted, one completed. Epic 8.3 (Rust Infrastructure) is now complete. Sprint progress moves from 30/34 to 31/34 (91%).\n   785→\n   786→**Note:** Ralph state-snapshot shows 8-5 still as `review` and 8-6 as `backlog` -- state tracking desync persists. sprint-status.yaml (source of truth) shows both as `done`.\n   787→\n   788→---\n   789→\n   790→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   791→\n   792→### Bugs Discovered\n   793→\n   794→| Severity | Story | Description | Fixed? |\n   795→|----------|-------|-------------|--------|\n   796→| CRITICAL | 8-6 | `package.json` `files` array missing `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` and `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` -- templates existed in source but were not shipped in npm package | Yes |\n   797→| MEDIUM | 8-6 | NFR9 violation -- `env.ts` grew to 307 lines (> 300 limit). Merged `buildRustImage` and `buildGenericImage` into `buildSimpleImage` helper | Yes (299 lines) |\n   798→| MEDIUM | 8-6 | Unreadable nested ternary in `resolveDockerfileTemplate`. Replaced with `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` lookup map | Yes |\n   799→| MEDIUM | 8-6 | Stale comment in hash-skip section of env.ts | Yes |\n   800→| MEDIUM | 8-6 | AGENTS.md stale -- didn't document Rust as supported project type | Yes |\n   801→\n   802→The CRITICAL `package.json` files bug is noteworthy: this would have caused npm-installed users to silently fail on `codeharness verify-env build` for Rust projects. Caught only because the verifier ran the actual CLI in a container.\n   803→\n   804→### Workarounds / Tech Debt\n   805→\n   806→- **Task 5.2 deviation:** Story specified copying `Cargo.toml/Cargo.lock/src` into build context. Dev agent correctly identified this as a tools-only image (project mounted at runtime) and followed `buildGenericImage` pattern instead. Deviation documented but not a true workaround.\n   807→- **Build timeout divergence:** `buildRustImage` uses 300s timeout (vs 120s for others) because `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` compiles from source. Minor pattern deviation.\n   808→\n   809→### Verification Gaps\n   810→\n   811→- **AC7 (Docker-in-Docker):** Escalated -- genuinely impossible in black-box container verification.\n   812→- **AC8 (npm test in black-box):** Escalated -- cannot run full test suite inside verification container.\n   813→- **Cache invalidation issue:** After fixing `package.json`, `codeharness verify-env build` reported \"up to date (cached)\" because hash only covers `dist/` contents. Had to manually invalidate stored dist hash. This means template-only changes can be silently missed by the build cache.\n   814→\n   815→### Code Quality (not fixed)\n   816→\n   817→- **LOW:** Tests cast `'rust'` as `ReturnType<typeof detectStack>` unnecessarily.\n   818→- **Coverage gap:** No test for `buildSimpleImage` timeout parameter propagation (Rust 300s vs generic 120s).\n   819→- **Coverage gap:** AC7 integration test marked `integration-required` -- needs Docker to verify.\n   820→\n   821→### Tooling / Infrastructure\n   822→\n   823→- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not installed (recurring since Epic 7).\n   824→- **Showboat re-verification skipped:** showboat not installed (recurring).\n   825→- **No observability telemetry in verification container:** All 7 ACs showed no VictoriaLogs entries. Same root cause as previous stories -- no Docker-in-Docker.\n   826→\n   827→---\n   828→\n   829→## 3. What Went Well\n   830→\n   831→- **CRITICAL bug caught during verification.** The missing `files` entries in `package.json` would have broken npm-distributed Rust support entirely. Black-box verification earned its keep.\n   832→- **Code review drove real refactoring.** `env.ts` was brought back under the 300-line limit via `buildSimpleImage` consolidation and the `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` lookup map. Both improve readability.\n   833→- **Full story lifecycle in ~23 minutes.** create-story (11:10) through verify (11:28) plus code-review. Consistent with session velocity.\n   834→- **Epic 8.3 complete.** All Rust infrastructure stories (8-5, 8-6) done. Rust projects can now generate Dockerfiles and build verification images.\n   835→\n   836→---\n   837→\n   838→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   839→\n   840→- **State tracking desync worsened.** `.state-snapshot.json` shows 8-5 as `review` and 8-6 as `backlog` while `sprint-status.yaml` correctly shows both as `done`. Three consecutive addendums have flagged this. The state-snapshot is now 2 stories behind reality.\n   841→- **Build cache hashes only `dist/` contents.** Template file changes don't invalidate the cache. This caused a false \"up to date\" during verification and required manual hash invalidation. A real user would not know to do this.\n   842→- **Escalated ACs are accumulating.** 8-6 has 2 escalated ACs (AC7, AC8) that need Docker-in-Docker. 8-5 had similar escalations. These are not being tracked for follow-up.\n   843→\n   844→---\n   845→\n   846→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   847→\n   848→### Repeat\n   849→\n   850→- **Black-box verification catches packaging bugs that unit tests never will.** The `package.json` files array bug is invisible to `npm test` but fatal to users. Always verify in a container.\n   851→- **Code review before verification.** The `env.ts` refactoring (307 -> 299 lines) happened during review, before the verifier saw the code. Clean code is easier to verify.\n   852→\n   853→### Avoid\n   854→\n   855→- **Do not assume `files` array in `package.json` is complete.** Every new template file needs a corresponding entry. Consider adding a CI check that verifies all `templates/` files are listed in `package.json` `files`.\n   856→- **Do not rely on `dist/` hash for build cache invalidation.** Template changes are invisible to the current cache. Fix the hash to include `templates/` directory.\n   857→\n   858→---\n   859→\n   860→## 6. Action Items\n   861→\n   862→### Fix Now (before next session)\n   863→\n   864→- [ ] Reconcile `.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-status.yaml` -- 8-5 and 8-6 should be `done`, sprint done count should be 31\n   865→- [ ] Verify `package.json` `files` array includes all `templates/` files (prevent recurrence of CRITICAL bug)\n   866→\n   867→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   868→\n   869→- [ ] **Extend build cache hash to include `templates/` directory** -- template-only changes currently bypass cache invalidation\n   870→- [ ] **Add CI check that all `templates/*` files are listed in `package.json` `files` array** -- prevents shipping incomplete npm packages\n   871→- [ ] **Track escalated ACs** -- 8-5 and 8-6 each have ACs that need Docker-in-Docker integration testing\n   872→- [ ] **Add timeout propagation test** for `buildSimpleImage` (Rust 300s vs