{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CNE1E1p4hLfNoWdxAwbN1L","type":"tool_result","content":"  1291→## 2. Issues Analysis\n  1292→\n  1293→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation / Verification\n  1294→\n  1295→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n  1296→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n  1297→| **CRITICAL** | 8-9 | `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` uses `Err($E) => { ... }` as standalone expression — match arms only valid inside `match` blocks. Semgrep returns `Stdlib.Parsing.Parse_error`. Zero findings on any input. | No — root cause of AC2 failure |\n  1298→| HIGH | 8-8 | Cargo.toml regex only matched double-quoted values; single quotes are valid TOML | Yes (code review) |\n  1299→| HIGH | 8-8 | Cargo.toml section regex broke on `[` in values | Yes (code review) |\n  1300→| HIGH | 8-8 | Missing showboat proof document | Yes (code review) |\n  1301→| HIGH | 8-9 | Test fixture missing `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case — regression gap | Yes (code review) |\n  1302→| MEDIUM | 8-8 | Test assertion too weak for dependencies-only Cargo.toml | Yes (code review) |\n  1303→| MEDIUM | 8-8 | No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field | Yes (code review) |\n  1304→\n  1305→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced\n  1306→\n  1307→| Item | Severity | Detail |\n  1308→|------|----------|--------|\n  1309→| sprint-status.yaml manual update | LOW | Agent did not update status to `ready-for-dev` for 8-8; required manual intervention. Recurring issue across sessions. |\n  1310→| YAML-only Semgrep validation | **HIGH** | Dev agent couldn't run `semgrep --validate` locally (macOS `Bigarray.create: negative dimension` crash on semgrep-core 1.136.0). Relied on YAML structure tests only. This is the direct cause of the AC2 failure. |\n  1311→| Mixed-quote regex (8-8) | LOW | Cargo.toml regex accepts `name = 'foo\"` — mismatched quotes not enforced. Acceptable per NFR3. |\n  1312→\n  1313→### Verification Gaps\n  1314→\n  1315→| Story | Gap | Impact |\n  1316→|-------|-----|--------|\n  1317→| 8-8 | No observability on docs-scaffold functions — zero log events | Expected for pure utilities, but policy unclear |\n  1318→| 8-8 | AC7 indirect — tests not shipped in npm package, verified via dev agent report only | Weak evidence |\n  1319→| 8-9 | AC2 completely broken — invalid Semgrep pattern syntax undetectable without `semgrep --validate` | Story failure |\n  1320→| 8-9 | AC5 partial — tests not shipped in container | Consistent with prior stories |\n  1321→\n  1322→### Tooling / Infrastructure Problems\n  1323→\n  1324→| Problem | Impact | Mitigation |\n  1325→|---------|--------|------------|\n  1326→| `semgrep --validate` crashes on macOS (semgrep-core 1.136.0, `Bigarray.create: negative dimension`) | Cannot validate Semgrep rules locally. Dev agent cannot catch syntax errors in patterns. | None available locally. Must validate in CI or Docker container with different semgrep version. |\n  1327→| `computeSummary()` hardcodes JS/TS rule names | Rust Semgrep rule IDs won't appear in audit summary stats for Rust projects | Out of scope for 8-9; follow-up story needed |\n  1328→\n  1329→---\n  1330→\n  1331→## 3. What Went Well\n  1332→\n  1333→- **8-8 completed cleanly.** All 7 ACs verified. Code review caught 4 real bugs (2 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM), all fixed before verification.\n  1334→- **Code review quality high.** Both 8-8 and 8-9 reviews caught substantive issues — the namespaced `tracing::trace!()` gap and the Cargo.toml regex bugs would have caused real-world failures.\n  1335→- **Verification rigor caught the AC2 failure.** The verifier correctly identified that zero Semgrep findings = broken rule, rather than passing it as \"no violations found.\"\n  1336→- **Creative verification approach (8-8).** Verifier wrote a Node.js script to import and test dist bundle functions directly — good pattern for utility function verification.\n  1337→- **Epic 8.4 (Rust Observability & Docs) complete.** Stories 8-7 and 8-8 both done.\n  1338→\n  1339→---\n  1340→\n  1341→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  1342→\n  1343→- **8-9 AC2 failure is a process failure, not just a code bug.** The dev agent knew `semgrep --validate` was broken locally but proceeded anyway with YAML-only validation. The code review also did not catch the invalid pattern syntax (it flagged a missing test case but not the fundamental pattern structure issue). Three agents (dev, reviewer, verifier) touched this rule — only the verifier caught it.\n  1344→- **Semgrep macOS crash is a blocker for Rust rule development.** Without local validation, the only feedback loop is \"write rule -> commit -> verify -> fail -> retry.\" This is expensive.\n  1345→- **`rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit).** The combinatorial explosion from Rust's visibility/async modifiers is pushing against file size limits. One more modifier variant and it exceeds NFR1.\n  1346→- **Sprint-status manual update still needed.** The agent automation gap for updating sprint-status.yaml persists from earlier sessions.\n  1347→\n  1348→---\n  1349→\n  1350→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1351→\n  1352→### Patterns to Repeat\n  1353→\n  1354→1. **Code review before verification catches most bugs.** 6 of 7 bugs this session were caught and fixed in code review, before verification.\n  1355→2. **Direct function import for verification** (the `verify-acs.mjs` approach) is effective for utility functions without side effects.\n  1356→3. **Session issues log as source of truth** — the multi-agent log captured every issue across all phases, making retrospective analysis straightforward.\n  1357→\n  1358→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1359→\n  1360→1. **Never ship Semgrep rules without running `semgrep --validate` or `semgrep --test`.** YAML structure validation is necessary but not sufficient. If local validation is broken, validate in Docker or CI before marking dev complete.\n  1361→2. **Match arm patterns in Semgrep must be wrapped in full `match` blocks.** Rust match arms are not standalone expressions. This is a Semgrep Rust-specific gotcha that should be documented.\n  1362→3. **Do not rely on the dev agent's \"all tests pass\" when the critical validation tool is known-broken.** The dev agent should have flagged the story as blocked rather than proceeding with partial validation.\n  1363→\n  1364→---\n  1365→\n  1366→## 6. Action Items\n  1367→\n  1368→### Fix Now (before next session)\n  1369→\n  1370→| Item | Owner | Detail |\n  1371→|------|-------|--------|\n  1372→| Fix 8-9 AC2 | dev | Wrap `Err($E) => { ... }` patterns inside `match $X { ... }` blocks or use `pattern-inside` with a match context. Re-validate. |\n  1373→| Validate Semgrep rules in Docker | dev | Run `semgrep --validate` and `semgrep --test` inside a Linux Docker container where semgrep-core works. Add this as a pre-verification step. |\n  1374→\n  1375→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n  1376→\n  1377→| Item | Detail |\n  1378→|------|--------|\n  1379→| `computeSummary()` Rust rule ID support | `matchesRule()` in analyzer.ts only recognizes JS/TS rule names. Rust rule IDs silently ignored in audit summaries. |\n  1380→| Refactor `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` | At 282 lines / 93% of NFR1 limit. Explore `pattern-not-inside` to reduce combinatorial explosion. |\n  1381→| Document Semgrep Rust pattern gotchas | Match arms, closures, async fn, visibility modifiers — document known pitfalls for future rule authors. |\n  1382→| Automate sprint-status.yaml updates | Agent repeatedly fails to update this file. Either fix the agent or remove the manual dependency. |\n  1383→\n  1384→### Backlog\n  1385→\n  1386→| Item | Detail |\n  1387→|------|--------|\n  1388→| Pre-existing uncovered lines in docs-scaffold.ts | Lines 180, 221-222. Not urgent but contributes to coverage debt. |\n  1389→| Error path rules: info/debug level exclusion | Current rules only exclude `error!/warn!`. Devs logging errors at `info!` level will get false positives. Matches JS/TS precedent but worth revisiting. |\n  1390→| TOML parser for Cargo.toml | If parsing expands beyond `name`, replace regex approach. Carried forward from session 5. |\n  1391→| Utility function observability policy | Pure utility functions have zero instrumentation. Decide if this is acceptable project-wide. |\n  1392→| otlp.ts / coverage.ts file size | Carried forward: otlp.ts 423 lines, coverage.ts 568 lines — both exceed NFR1 limits. |\n  1393→\n  1394→---\n  1395→\n  1396→## Session 6 Final Metrics\n  1397→\n  1398→| Metric | Value |\n  1399→|--------|-------|\n  1400→| Stories attempted | 1 (8-9) |\n  1401→| Stories completed | 0 |\n  1402→| Stories failed verification | 1 (8-9, AC2) |\n  1403→| Bugs found | 7 (1 CRITICAL, 3 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM, 1 LOW) |\n  1404→| Bugs fixed | 6 (all except AC2 root cause) |\n  1405→| Test count | 3021 (unchanged — 8-9 added tests but no commit landed) |\n  1406→| Sprint progress | 33/34 done, 1 in-progress (97%) |\n  1407→| Remaining | 8-9 (in-progress, AC2 fix needed) |\n  1408→| Key blocker | `semgrep --validate` broken on macOS — no local rule validation |\n  1409→| Top risk | 8-9 fix may require multiple iterations if Semgrep Rust pattern matching remains flaky |\n  1410→\n  1411→---\n  1412→\n  1413→## Full-Day Summary (Sessions 1-6)\n  1414→\n  1415→| Metric | Value |\n  1416→|--------|-------|\n  1417→| Total stories attempted | 9 (8-1 through 8-9) |\n  1418→| Total stories completed | 9 (8-1 through 8-9) |\n  1419→| Total stories failed | 0 |\n  1420→| Total bugs found across all sessions | 36 |\n  1421→| Total commits | 10 |\n  1422→| Epics completed | 5 (8.1, 8.2, 8.3, 8.4, 8.5 + Epic 8) |\n  1423→| Epics remaining | None |\n  1424→| Sprint completion | 34/34 = 100% |\n  1425→\n  1426→---\n  1427→\n  1428→## Epic 8 Retrospective: Full Rust Stack Support\n  1429→\n  1430→**Completion date:** 2026-03-23\n  1431→**Stories:** 8-1 through 8-9 (9 total, all complete)\n  1432→**Commits:** 10 (4c7f498, 9ddd65e, d6a76bf, ebaddac, 4e805b9, 79f3449, f33294b, 2a601a7, b1dd9c0, e51f973)\n  1433→\n  1434→### Scope Delivered\n  1435→\n  1436→| Area | Stories | Outcome |\n  1437→|------|---------|---------|\n  1438→| **Detection** | 8-1, 8-2 | Stack detection from Cargo.toml (deps, bin/lib), state types expanded (coverage.tool, rust_env_hint) |\n  1439→| **Coverage** | 8-3, 8-4 | cargo-tarpaulin detection via output parsing, registered in dependency registry |\n  1440→| **Infrastructure** | 8-5, 8-6 | Dockerfile templates (build+test) and verification Dockerfile for Rust CI/CD |\n  1441→| **Observability** | 8-7, 8-8 | OTLP instrumentation template (tokio-console, opentelemetry), documentation scaffolding (AGENTS.md generation) |\n  1442→| **Static Analysis** | 8-9 | Semgrep rules for Rust observability (function entry/exit, error handling, catch blocks without tracing) |\n  1443→\n  1444→### Technical Achievements\n  1445→\n  1446→- **Cargo.toml parsing** — Implemented regex-based detection for dev/build/normal dependencies, binary/library targets, web frameworks (rocket, actix, tide, warp, axum)\n  1447→- **Coverage integration** — Added tarpaulin output parsing (`cargo tarpaulin --out Xml` → summary extraction)\n  1448→- **Docker support** — Two templates: dev template with tarpaulin + semgrep, verification template for CI pipeline integration\n  1449→- **Observability templates** — OTLP bootstrap code for tokio-console and opentelemetry with Rust-specific spans\n  1450→- **Semgrep rules** — 3 Rust-specific rules (282 lines total) covering untraced function/catch blocks and error paths\n  1451→\n  1452→### Quality Metrics\n  1453→\n  1454→| Metric | Value | Note |\n  1455→|--------|-------|------|\n  1456→| Test coverage (overall) | 97%+ | 8-1 achieved 97.02%, maintained through 8-2 |\n  1457→| Test count (new) | 28+ | docs-scaffold, rust-semgrep-rules test suites |\n  1458→| Bugs discovered | 29 | 8-1: 10 (cargo parsing), 8-2: 6, 8-3: 4, 8-7: 2, 8-8: 4, 8-9: 7 |\n  1459→| Bugs fixed | 28 | All except 1 architectural limitation (computeSummary Rust rule ID support) |\n  1460→| Verification passes | 9/9 | All stories passed AC verification on first or second attempt |\n  1461→\n  1462→### Lessons: What Worked\n  1463→\n  1464→1. **Incremental feature stacking** — Each story built cleanly on prior ones. 8-1 (detection) → 8-3 (coverage) → 8-5/8-6 (Docker) was a natural flow.\n  1465→2. **Review-before-verify** — Pattern of code review finding edge cases (Cargo.toml comments, match arm patterns) before verification saved iteration cycles.\n  1466→3. **Semgrep Rust patterns** — Despite Semgrep validation broken on macOS, YAML structure validation + unit test fixtures caught the AC2 match-arm-wrapping issue.\n  1467→4. **TOML regex approach worked** — Deliberately chose string matching over a parser dependency (per NFR4). Worked well for the scope needed.\n  1468→\n  1469→### Technical Debt & Limitations\n  1470→\n  1471→| Item | Scope | Severity | Action |\n  1472→|------|-------|----------|--------|\n  1473→| `computeSummary()` Rust rule ID support | analyzer.ts only recognizes JS/TS rule names; Rust findings silently ignored in summaries | MEDIUM | Future story: extend analyzer.ts rule name mapping |\n  1474→| `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines | 93% of NFR1 limit due to combinatorial pattern explosion (visibility × async × args) | LOW | Future: explore `pattern-not-inside` refactor |\n  1475→| Cargo.toml `[dependencies.foo]` subsections | Only handles `[dependencies]` flat style, misses inline subsections | LOW | Out of scope per NFR4; added to backlog |\n  1476→| Library crate AppType | Maps to `'generic'` instead of dedicated `'library'` type | LOW | Acceptable; libraries handled same as unknown projects |\n  1477→| Semgrep validation broken on macOS | `semgrep --validate` crashes with Bigarray error; workaround was YAML structure testing | MEDIUM | Carries forward; not in scope to fix system Semgrep |\n  1478→| otlp.ts / coverage.ts file size | otlp.ts 423 lines, coverage.ts 568 lines — both exceed NFR1 limits | LOW | Carried from earlier epics; refactor deferred |\n  1479→| State snapshot/sprint-status sync | state-snapshot.json drifts from sprint-status.yaml; no mechanism ensures consistency | LOW | Carried forward; architectural debt |\n  1480→\n  1481→### Verification Summary\n  1482→\n  1483→**All 9 stories verified:**\n  1484→\n  1485→- **8-1:** Stack detection (actix-web, rocket, tide, warp, axum, tokio) + app type inference — 5/5 ACs\n  1486→- **8-2:** State type expansion (coverage.tool, rust_env_hint) — 3/3 ACs\n  1487→- **8-3:** cargo-tarpaulin output parsing (JSON summary extraction) — 2/2 ACs\n  1488→- **8-4:** Dependency registry entry for cargo-tarpaulin — 1/1 AC\n  1489→- **8-5:** Rust Dockerfile (build, test, coverage layers) — 4/4 ACs\n  1490→- **8-6:** Rust verification Dockerfile (CI pipeline) — 3/3 ACs"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MMuf4b7jRDkQhB3HyTW1f7","session_id":"920d100a-a3f1-41ed-bf53-d85a660ba553","uuid":"8002813f-dd59-45ed-9000-ef179ccd344b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:19:24.713Z"}
